# WoPeD Next

Petri net editor and workflow analysis tool. Migrated from Java Swing to Vue.js 3.

## Tech Stack
- Vue.js 3 (Composition API with `<script setup>`)
- Vite as build tool
- Pinia for state management
- vue-i18n for internationalization (DE/EN)
- vue-konva for canvas rendering
- TypeScript for type definitions
- nginx for production (Docker)
- GitHub Pages for deployment

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/     # Vue components grouped by feature
│   ├── canvas/     # Konva canvas elements (Place, Transition, Arc, etc.)
│   ├── editor/     # Main editor components
│   ├── simulation/ # Quantitative simulation
│   ├── token-game/ # Token game
│   └── analysis/   # Analysis panels
├── stores/         # Pinia stores (petriNet, config, tokenGame, simulation)
├── services/       # Business logic (file, analysis, simulation, templates)
├── types/          # TypeScript interfaces
├── utils/          # Helper functions (geometry, layout, routing)
└── i18n/           # Translations (en.ts, de.ts)
```

## Commands
- `npm run dev` - Development server (http://localhost:5173)
- `npm run build` - Production build
- `docker compose up --build` - Start Docker

## Git Workflow
- Commit and push only with explicit user permission
- When permitted: Create meaningful commit message, then commit and push

## Important Conventions
- All UI texts must be translated (`$t('key')`)
- Use CSS variables for theming (`var(--color-bg)`, `var(--color-text)`)
- Dark mode via `data-theme="dark"` on `<html>`
- Generate IDs with `nanoid()`
- Petri net elements: Place, Transition, Arc, Operator, SubProcess
- All rules, skills, comments and docs must be in English

## Stores
| Store | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `petriNet` | Net data, viewport, selection, history |
| `config` | Theme, language, editor settings (persisted) |
| `tokenGame` | Marking, enabled transitions, statistics |
| `simulation` | Simulation config, results, resources |

## Important Services
- `fileService` - PNML/JSON import/export
- `SimulationEngine` - Discrete event simulation
- `petriNetTemplates` - Educational example nets
- `metricsCalculator` - Process metrics calculation
